Mauritius needs capacity for another
600,000 airline passenger seats in the next two years to keep up
with an increase in hotel accommodation, Le Mauricien reported,
citing Patrice Legris, chief executive officer of the countryâ€™s
hotel and restaurant association.  The number of hotel rooms climbed 15 percent since 2008
while passenger seats rose 2 percent, the Port Louis-based
